{
  "page": "Addam Osgrey",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For others with the same name, see <a href=\"/index.php/Addam\" title=\"Addam\">Addam</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Osgrey\" title=\"House Osgrey\"><img alt=\"House Osgrey.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/50px-House_Osgrey.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/75px-House_Osgrey.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/100px-House_Osgrey.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Addam Osgrey</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Osgrey\" title=\"House Osgrey\"><img alt=\"House Osgrey.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/50px-House_Osgrey.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/75px-House_Osgrey.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/100px-House_Osgrey.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Osgrey\" title=\"House Osgrey\">House Osgrey</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_183_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">183&#160;AC</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/184_AC\" title=\"184 AC\">184&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Standfast\" title=\"Standfast\">Standfast</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafaddam_osgrey.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafaddam_osgrey.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/196_AC\" title=\"196 AC\">196&#160;AC</a> <small>(aged 12)</small><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Redgrass_Field\" title=\"Redgrass Field\">Redgrass Field</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_Osgrey\" title=\"Eustace Osgrey\">Eustace Osgrey</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Sworn_Sword\" title=\"The Sworn Sword\">The Sworn Sword</a></i> <small>(mentioned)</small></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Addam Osgrey</b> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Squire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Squire\">squire</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Osgrey\" title=\"House Osgrey\">House Osgrey</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron II Targaryen</a>. He was the third son of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_Osgrey\" title=\"Eustace Osgrey\">Eustace Osgrey</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Standfast\" title=\"Standfast\">Standfast</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Character\">Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Addam_Osgrey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Addam was fond of blackberries. According to his father, he was a brave boy. He sometimes wore an Osgrey squire's doublet of green and gold checks, and white woolen breeches.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Addam_Osgrey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Addam served as a page and then as a squire at <a href=\"/index.php/Coldmoat\" title=\"Coldmoat\">Coldmoat</a>, the seat of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Webber\" title=\"Wyman Webber\">Wyman Webber</a>, his father's friend. During his time at Coldmoat, a love grew between Addam and Lord Wyman's daughter, <a href=\"/index.php/Rohanne_Webber\" title=\"Rohanne Webber\">Rohanne</a>, two years younger than him. Addam would pick blackberries from the thicket on Standfast's hill for Rohanne, and they would eat them with cream. However, their innocent romance never went beyond a few kisses. Addam's father, Ser Eustace, came to Coldmoat to propose a <a href=\"/index.php/Marriage\" title=\"Marriage\">marriage</a> between the two children. Lord Wyman refused him, however, possibly due to Eustace's growing <a href=\"/index.php/Traitor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Traitor\">traitorous</a> leanings towards the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Blackfyre\" title=\"House Blackfyre\">Blackfyre</a> cause. Though his refusal was polite, as Eustace left he heard Lord Wyman laughing with his <a href=\"/index.php/Castellan\" title=\"Castellan\">castellan</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Lucas_Inchfield\" title=\"Lucas Inchfield\">Lucas Inchfield</a>. Lord Wyman then had Rohanne married to another of his squires, while Ser Eustace refused to ever return to Coldmoat for thirteen years.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"First Blackfyre Rebellion\">First Blackfyre Rebellion</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/196_AC\" title=\"196 AC\">196&#160;AC</a>, Ser Eustace fought on the side of the pretender <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">Daemon I Blackfyre</a>. His three sons went to war with him, including Addam, twelve years old, as his father's squire. During the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Redgrass_Field\" title=\"Battle of the Redgrass Field\">Battle of the Redgrass Field</a>, Addam was trying to protect his wounded brother, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Harrold_Osgrey\" title=\"Harrold Osgrey\">Harrold</a>, when a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Smallwood\" title=\"House Smallwood\">House Smallwood</a> cut off his arm with an ax. Addam's brothers also died in the battle, and afterwards his sister <a href=\"/index.php/Alysanne_Osgrey\" title=\"Alysanne Osgrey\">Alysanne</a> was sent to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> as a <a href=\"/index.php/Hostage\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hostage\">hostage</a> for Eustace's pardon. After Eustace brought home the bones of his sons and allowed Alysanne to be taken away, Addam's mother committed suicide by throwing herself from the top of Standfast. Eustace buried his wife and sons at Standfast by the blackberry bushes his sons had loved to pick.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord Wyman Webber also fought in the battle, on the side of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a>, and his squire (Rohanne's husband) was slain, making her a widow at the age of ten. However, Rohanne mourned only for Addam, not for her husband; she blamed Ser Eustace for his death, and held a grudge against the knight thereafter.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/211_AC\" title=\"211 AC\">211&#160;AC</a>, due to growing tensions with Lady Rohanne Webber, Ser Eustace Osgrey took on Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a> as a <a href=\"/index.php/Sworn_sword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sworn sword\">sworn sword</a>. Duncan's squire, <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Egg</a>, was outfitted in Addam's old squire's clothing. On Ser Eustace's behalf, Duncan went to Coldmoat to pay a <a href=\"/index.php/Blood_price\" title=\"Blood price\">blood price</a> for his <a href=\"/index.php/Bennis_of_the_Brown_Shield\" title=\"Bennis of the Brown Shield\">fellow sworn sword</a>'s assault on <a href=\"/index.php/Wolmer\" title=\"Wolmer\">one of Rohanne's men</a>, and to request that Lady Rohanne take down the dam on the <a href=\"/index.php/Chequy_Water\" title=\"Chequy Water\">Chequy Water</a> that blocked the stream from reaching Osgrey lands. However, she refused both petitions. Duncan, having heard the story of Addam and Rohanne's childhood fondness from Ser Eustace, made the mistake of appealing to Rohanne in Addam's name, for which she struck him in fury. Duncan eventually defeated Rohanne's <a href=\"/index.php/Lucas_Inchfield\" title=\"Lucas Inchfield\">champion</a> in a <a href=\"/index.php/Trial_by_combat\" title=\"Trial by combat\">trial by combat</a> in the Chequy Water, and afterwards Eustace and Rohanne reconciled. She visited Addam's grave at Standfast, and when she knelt before the blackberries and began to weep, Eustace comforted her. They spent the night talking of their families, and married the next day, which allowed Rohanne to keep ruling Coldmoat per her father's will.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Addam_Osgrey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>They died good deaths, fighting bravely for <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">the king</a>, and I brought them <a href=\"/index.php/Standfast\" title=\"Standfast\">home</a> and buried them among the blackberries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_Osgrey\" title=\"Eustace Osgrey\">Eustace Osgrey</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Duncan:</b> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_Osgrey\" title=\"Eustace Osgrey\">Eustace</a> told me <a href=\"/index.php/Rohanne_Webber\" title=\"Rohanne Webber\">she</a> was fond of the boy.<br />\n<b>Sefton:</b> Fond? She loved the boy, and him her. It never went beyond a kiss or two, but... it was Addam she wept for after <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Redgrass_Field\" title=\"Battle of the Redgrass Field\">the Redgrass Field</a>, not the husband she hardly knew. She blames Ser Eustace for his death, and rightly so. The boy was twelve.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">Septon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Sefton_Staunton\" title=\"Sefton Staunton\">Sefton</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I scarce remember Addam any longer. It was more than half my life ago. I remember that I loved him, though. I have not loved any of the others.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Rohanne_Webber\" title=\"Rohanne Webber\">Rohanne Webber</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Addam_Osgrey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><